[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    370[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    371[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 4: Score Current Membership with Batch Transform
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    372[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    373[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *The pseudocode calls this `score_membership(model, calibrator, active_members, scoring_date)`. SageMaker Batch Transform applies the trained model to a large dataset without deploying a persistent endpoint. This is ideal for weekly scoring of the full membership: you pay only for the compute time used during the batch job.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    374[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    375[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    376[0m:[38;5;10m[49m from sagemaker.transformer import Transformer
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    377[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    378[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    379[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def score_membership_batch(model_uri: str, members_df: pd.DataFrame, scoring_date: str) -> str:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    380[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    381[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Score all active members using SageMaker Batch Transform.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    382[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    383[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Batch Transform is the right choice for weekly scoring of the full
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    384[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     membership. It spins up instances, processes all the data, writes results
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    385[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     to S3, and shuts down. No persistent endpoint to pay for between runs.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    386[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    387[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     For real-time scoring of individual members (e.g., when a high-signal
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    388[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     event occurs), you'd deploy a SageMaker real-time endpoint instead.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    389[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    390[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    391[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         model_uri: S3 URI of the trained model artifact.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    392[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         members_df: DataFrame of current members with features.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    393[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         scoring_date: ISO date string for partitioning results.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    394[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    395[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    396[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         S3 URI where the scoring results are written.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    397[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    398[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     session = sagemaker.Session()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    399[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    400[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Prepare the scoring input: features only, no label, no header.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    401[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Same column order as training.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    402[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     scoring_data = members_df[FEATURE_COLUMNS]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    403[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     scoring_path = "/tmp/churn_scoring_input.csv"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    404[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     scoring_data.to_csv(scoring_path, header=False, index=False)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    405[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    406[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Upload scoring input to S3.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    407[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     scoring_key = f"{FEATURES_PREFIX}scoring_date={scoring_date}/members.csv"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    408[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     s3_client.upload_file(scoring_path, ML_BUCKET, scoring_key)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    409[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     scoring_uri = f"s3://{ML_BUCKET}/{scoring_key}"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    410[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    411[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Create a SageMaker model from the training artifact.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    412[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     region = session.boto_region_name
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    413[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     container = sagemaker.image_uris.retrieve(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    414[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         framework="xgboost",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    415[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         region=region,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    416[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         version="1.7-1",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    417[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    418[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    419[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     model = sagemaker.model.Model(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    420[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         image_uri=container,
